&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;● Work closely with campus leads to help screen and interview candidates to hire intern and new&lt;br&gt;graduate classes&lt;br&gt;● Represent Five Rings in leading on-campus events and initiatives, such as career fairs,&lt;br&gt;information sessions, and coffee chats&lt;br&gt;● Assist in building out and running early identification programs&lt;br&gt;● Conduct internship midpoint and final check-ins&lt;br&gt;● Develop and manage key stakeholder relationships with senior management&lt;br&gt;● Collaborate with different members of the Recruiting team on various projects and improve&lt;br&gt;processes where needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;● Bachelor’s degree&lt;br&gt;● 2 - 4 years as a recruitment coordinator or recruiter, ideally on a campus team&lt;br&gt;● Self-starter with strong problem-solving skills, able to take initiative, navigate ambiguity, and&lt;br&gt;proactively identify solutions without needing constant direction&lt;br&gt;● Ability to work in a fast-paced, startup environment&lt;br&gt;● Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;br&gt;● Strong organizational and project management skills&lt;br&gt;● Ability to confidently interact with all levels of management&lt;br&gt;● Demonstrate good judgment and a positive attitude&lt;br&gt;● Maintain strict confidentiality of data and information&lt;br&gt;● Effectively manage multiple priorities, deadlines, and tasks&lt;br&gt;● Experience working both independently and collaboratively&lt;/p&gt;
